ing> undoStack; // Undo stack char key; cout << \\"> \\"; getline(cin, text); while (true) { cout << \\"> \\"; cin >> key; // Input buffer cout << flush; if (key == 'z') { // If user pressed 'Z' if (undoStack.empty()) cout << \\"Nothing to undo.\\" << endl; else { // If there is something to undo text = undoStack.top(); undoStack.pop(); cout << \\"Redoing changes...\\" << endl; } } else if (key == 'Z') { // If user pressed 'z' if (undoStack.empty()) cout << \\"Nothing to redo.\\" << endl; else { // If there is something to redo undoStack.push(text); cout << \\"Undoing changes...\\" << endl; } } else { // If user inputted a character text += key; } cout << \\"> \\" << endl; } return 0; } \`\`\` This basic text editor allows the user to input and store text in memory. It only supports 1 undo and redo operation. If the user has not performed any undo or redo operation, it prints \\"Nothing to undo\\" and \\"Nothing to redo\\" messages. This program serves as a starting point. To enhance its functionality or to implement more complex features, you may modify the code"},{"prompt":"Rewrite the following text to improve/correct it. Text: Subjet: Importnat Updtae on Comapny Polciy Regrading Rmeote Work Daer Taem, I'm wrting to you today with an imprtant upadte reagrding our compnay's rmeote work ploicy. We've been clsely monitroing the onoging panedmic stiuation and its imapct on our wrokforce, and we've made some ncessary adjutsmnets in rseponse. Frstly, I want to akcnowledge your cncerns and asure you that this decsion was not tkaen lightly. The helath and saefty of our emloyees remain our top prority, and we understnad how critcal it is for many of us to mantain a felxible wroking envrionment during these chalenging times. In light of rcent devlopments, we've decieded to extend our rmeote work ploicy until fruther notice. This menas that all team mmebers who are currently wroking from home can contiue to do so. For those whsoe roles requrie them to be physiclaly present 